Hardware confirmed that the pBridge dHub SemaHub completes a 0-1-0
push/pop transition, proving the common clock, MMIO, command encoding and
query path. The HBO queue still ends with zero counts, but its empty and
full conditions are both set after PUSH. Determine whether channel 3 is
consuming a transient queue 7 token before the bounded poll observes it.

Follow Valve's complete stop and clear sequence for channel 3: stop command
queue 6, stop and clear the channel, wait for dHub busy and pending to
clear, then clear both queues. Restore both FIFOs and the channel after the
test. Capture both HBO query windows immediately after PUSH as well as at
the end of the poll.

Do not require the empty condition bit to remain cleared while the queue is
empty; hardware immediately reasserts that level and made the previous
diagnostic warn on a healthy dHub semaphore. Clear and verify only the full
condition before PUSH, then retain both post-operation conditions for
diagnostics.

No descriptor is submitted and no NAND command or media data is accessed.

